sentences: Duncan MacLennan (born 13 March 1985), better known by his stage name DCUP, is an Australian record producer, DJ and remixer.

He is best known for his collaboration with fellow Australian band Yolanda Be Cool on their international hit single "We No Speak Americano", which samples Renato Carosone and Nicola Salerno's 1956 hit "Tu Vuò Fà L'Americano", on the Australian indie label, Sweat It Out.
